				\begin{document}$$T\left( t \right) = A\mathop {\sum}\nolimits_i {e^{ - k_{{\mathrm{ET}},i}t}}$$\end{document} for the multiexponential energy-transfer dynamics. We determined the best value for Cxr (Eq. (2)) or Ccoop (Eq. (3)) by fitting our model to the data for one of the Yb3+ concentrations, indicated in Fig. 4 by the underlined value for x. Finally, we fitted our model to the data for all other Yb3+ concentrations, only optimizing the amplitudes A while keeping Cxr or Ccoop fixed.
